09/01/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Special prosecutors in Belgrade plan to establish a department that will investigate international drug trafficking gangs active in the Balkans, Special Organised Crime Prosecutor Miljko Radisavljevic said on Tuesday (January 8th). 
The new office will take over drug cases launched in Serbian courts and will actively co-operate with police and customs services in the region. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 08/01/08)
